cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.WM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a novel framework for providing wireless services to randomly roaming NOMA receivers (Rxs) in the sphere space by utilizing stochastic geometry tools. The paper also derives closed-form expressions for the outage probability and the ergodic rate of paired NOMA Rxs, which are related to information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper investigates the performance of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) enhanced unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV)-to-Everything (U2X) frameworks, which are related to networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.WM (Web and Internet Economics): The paper discusses the spectrum efficiency in both NOMA and orthogonal multiple access (OMA) enhanced U2X frameworks, which are related to web and internet economics.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a 3-Dimension framework for providing wireless services to randomly roaming NOMA receivers (Rxs) in the sphere space, which involves system and control aspects.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper investigates the performance of NOMA enhanced U2X frameworks, which can be used for multimedia applications such as video streaming and real-time communication.
